In letting or leasing we retain the property or right, and part only for a time with the use or enjoyment, receiving in return a lixed hire in money (maces). In selling we part absolutely with the property or right and receive in return a fixed price in money (pretium). The purchase-money is usually a sum paid once for all or else in agreed instalments: ,hire or rent is usually paid 'at regularly recurring intervals throughout the period of the contract. But the mode of payment is not apparently of the essence of the contracte.
